org.domainobject.jetlag.core.funclib

Annotation Type Function


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Function

    This annotation, when applied to a method, makes that method available in user interface. Methods without this annotation are considered internal to the library. Methods with this annotation must be public, but not all public methods must have this annotation. In other words, the set of methods exposed in the user interface is a subset of the public methods of a FunctionLibrary. This annotation can be applied both to instance methods and class methods.

    Function overloading

    As with Java, Jetlag functions may be overloaded by using different parameter lists.

    Author:
    Ayco Holleman

    • Element Detail

      • uiName

        public abstract String uiName
        Provides the name of the function within user interface. Function names used by the user need not map one-to-one to method names in a FunctionLibrary.
        Returns:
        The name of the function within jetlag's user interface
        Default:
        ""

      • ref

        public abstract String ref
        Provides the uiName of another method that implements the same user interface function, just with a larger method signature. In other words, the first parameters of the referenced method have the same type as the parameters of the method decorated using the ref attribute, but the referenced method has more parameters. Only the referenced method then needs to be described using annotation like Description. You must not specify the uiName and the ref attribute at the same time.
        Returns:
        Default:
        ""
